To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Kentucky Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

January 25, 2023 arrest and custody of Robin Brown, by the Winchester Police Department:

1. The arrest or incident report for this case;
2. Any booking or intake documents, including the time and location of custody, and personnel involved;
3. Any holding cell assignment logs, temporary detention room usage records, or custody housing logs from January 25 through January 31, 2023;
4. Any visitor sign-in sheets, logbooks, or interview room access logs for the duration of Ms. Brown’s custody during that same time period;
5. Any shift notes, watch commander logs, or internal duty officer summaries referencing her movement or custodial status;
6. Any transportation or custody transfer records, including documentation reflecting any handoffs between officers, agencies, or facilities;
7. Any dispatch logs or CAD (computer-aided dispatch) reports reflecting arrest, transport, or detention activity involving Ms. Brown;
8. Any body-worn camera footage recorded by Winchester Police Department officers during the arrest of Robin Brown on January 25, 2023, including approximately 10 minutes prior to the initial physical or verbal contact through her transport or transfer to custody.
9. Documentation reflecting the date and time of her release from custody or transfer to another agency, including associated forms.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Mike Bregenzer
